blic health and the leadership qualities required to negotiate it. This book is essential reading for students, academics, practitioners and policy-makers with an interest in governance and decision-making for public health.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aPublic health administrationxDecentralization. 0aPublic health administrationxResearch. 0aPublic healthxCitizen participation. 7aMEDICAL / Public Health.2bisacsh1 aHunter, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeckham, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311119634340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447304951423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447304951/original  a978-3-11-119634-3  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles